Class STGPRegression

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.AbstractPrototainer
      • objenome.Container
        • objenome.solver.evolve.GPContainer<TypedOrganism>

            • objenome.problem.STGPRegression
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractContainer, Prototainer

    public class STGPRegression
extends ProblemSTGP
    This template sets up EpochX to run the cubic regression benchmark with the STGP representation. Cubic regression involves evolving an equivalent function to the formula: x + x^2 + x^3 The following configuration is used:
  • Population.SIZE: 100
  • EvolutionaryStrategy.TERMINATION_CRITERIA: MaximumGenerations, TerminationFitness(0.0)
  • MaximumGenerations.MAXIMUM_GENERATIONS: 50
  • TypedOrganism.MAXIMUM_DEPTH: 6
  • Breeder.SELECTOR: TournamentSelector
  • TournamentSelector#TOURNAMENT_SIZE: 7
  • Breeder.OPERATORS: SubtreeCrossover, SubtreeMutation
  • SubtreeMutation.PROBABILITY: 0.0
  • SubtreeCrossover.PROBABILITY: 1.0
  • Initialiser.METHOD: FullInitialisation
  • RandomSequence.RANDOM_SEQUENCE: MersenneTwisterFast
  • TypedOrganism.SYNTAX: AddFunction, SubtractFunction, MultiplyFunction, DivisionProtectedFunction, VariableNode("X", Double)
  • TypedOrganism.RETURN_TYPE: Double
  • FitnessEvaluator.FUNCTION: HitsCount
  • HitsCount.POINT_ERROR: 0.01
  • TypedFitnessFunction.INPUT_VARIABLES: X
  • TypedFitnessFunction.INPUT_VALUE_SETS: [20 random values between -1.0 and +1.0]
  • HitsCount.EXPECTED_OUTPUTS: [correct output for input value sets]
Since:
2.0
